    "recap_headline": "University of Massachusets Athletics",
    "recap_text": "AKRON, Ohio -\nUniversity of Massachusetts baseball fell to Akron, 12-2, in game one of the weekend series on Friday afternoon at Skeeles Field.\nUMass moved to 4-6 overall on the season and 0-4 in the Mid-American Conference, while Akron improved to 8-9 overall and 2-2 in the league.\nTy Fox\nand\nMarc Willi\nled the team in hits with two each, while both registering an RBI. Fox recorded a double on the day.\nGavin O'Brien\nand\nReece McCarthy\nscored the two runs for the Minutemen.\nAkron scored two runs in the first inning on two RBI singles to take an early 2-0 lead.\nIn the top of the third, the Minutemen cut the deficit in half, making it a 2-1 game. With one out, O'Brien reached first on an error, before advancing to second. Fox, then singled to center field, sending O'Brien home.\nThe Zips put up five runs in the bottom of the third, which included an RBI double, to extend their lead to 7-1.\nReece McCarthy\nled off the fourth with a walk, before stealing second. Willi singled through the left side to help McCarthy across the plate and make it a 7-2 contest.\nAkron posted four more runs in the sixth frame to pull ahead, 11-2. The Zips scored another to win 12-2 in the seventh.\nCallen Powers\n(1-2) had the loss for Massachusetts, tossing five complete innings with seven runs, eight hits, a walk and six strikeouts.\nJosiah Ross (2-1) for Akron earned the win, allowing two runs on four hits, walking four and striking out four in four complete innings.\nUMass and Akron set for game two of the series on Saturday, March 14, at 1 p.m., at Skeeles Field."
